title: Gulf Coast Interstate Relay
description: The Gulf Coast Interstate (GCI) Relay, an innovative cycling relay event will take place April 5, 2014 Cycling teams will complete 263 miles from New Orleans, Louisiana to Pensacola Beach, Florida.
course: The GCI Relay start is in New Orleans, Louisiana, at the Comfort Suites Hotel on Bullard Avenue.The relay finish is in Pensacola Beach, Florida, Oceanfront on Casino Beach Road by The Pavilion. In between: mostly Lake bridges and swampland in Louisiana, beachfront through Mississippi (Gulfport, Biloxi, Pascagoula), mostly wide-open country roads through Alabama, except for the trek through the City of Mobile and over the Cochrane Bridge, 15 miles of country rode in Florida, through downtown Pensacola for a finish on Pensacola Beach.

title: Tradewinds Spring and Summer Training Series
description:
The Tradewinds Park State Road Race and Summer Training Series is geared to prep cyclist for the 2014 State Road Race which will be held in South Florida for the first time in Jensen Beach.  The Summer Series will also provide bi-weekly Wednesday Night racing throughout the summer to keep athletes engaged in their training. 

From April 9, 2014 to May 28, 2014 the State Road Race Training events will run every week (8 weeks).  The racing will have nightly payouts to keep each week competitive.  The 8 races will provide cyclists an opportunity to win a FREE entry to the 2014 State Road Race Championships.  The winner of the A and B race will receive a FREE entry.   Only one race entry per person.  Winning multiple race does not provide for multiple entries.  Entries are not transferrable.  

Beginning June 11, 2014 (Wednesday) the Summer Training Series will begin and repeat every other Wednesday.  If an event is cancelled due to inclement weather, the race will be held the following Wednesday.  All race information will be posted at: https://www.facebook.com/TeamPinkPanthers
The 2014 Summer Series will consist of a 4 races.  

The B race (Cat 4 & 5) riders will start at 6pm and will race for 45 minutes.  The A race (Cat 1, 2, 3) riders will start at 6:45pm and race for 60 minutes.
course: A closed 1.2 mile course located on the North Side of Tradewinds Park.
registration: Registration is on-site only -  CASH ONLY - The fee is $15 and includes the mandatory $3 fee to USA Cycling for insurance.  Juniors are $5.  All riders must have a valid USA Cycling License.  One Day Licenses will be available only for Cat 5 riders.
notes:
Cyclist - You will need to enter through the South Side of Tradewinds Park and follow the signs leading to the North Side of the Park

Registration Begins at 5:00pm
directions:
From I-95, exit at Sample Road and go west past the Florida's Turnpike overpass. The park has entrances on the north and south sides of Sample Road.

From Florida's Turnpike, exit at Sample Road. Turn left (west). The park's entrances are on the north and south sides of Sample Road, west of the Florida's Turnpike overpass.

From U.S. 441 (State Road 7), go east on Sample Road. The park's entrances are on the north and south sides of Sample Road before the Florida's Turnpike overpass.



Tradewinds Park
3600 W. Sample Rd., Coconut Creek, FL 33073
Office: 954-357-8870
